sing LangChain Agents</a>, I discussed the role of AI Agents and demonstrat=
ed an implementation using the LangChain framework. While it=E2=80=99s suit=
able for proofs of concept (POCs), it falls short for production environmen=
ts. In this post, I will offer a solution that is more adaptable to a produ=
ction-grade product. You=E2=80=99ll learn how to create a scalable, efficie=
nt system that=E2=80=99s better suited for real-world applications, giving =
you the tools to build more robust AI solutions.</p><h3 id=3D"0a20" class=
=3D"pd pe ie bc pf fz pg ga gb gc ph gd ge gf pi gg gh gi pj gj gk gl pk gm=
 gn pl bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">The Challenge with LangChain Agen=
ts in a Production Environment</h3><p id=3D"2152" class=3D"pw-post-body-par=
agraph oh oi ie oj b ok pm om on oo pn oq or gf po ot ou gi pp ow ox gl pq =
oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">The main challenge with Lang=
Chain Agents is that they grant full control to a single LLM through one la=
rge prompt, which manages the entire workflow. In production environments, =
more granular control is often required, especially as tasks evolve.</p><p =
id=3D"a5d3" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok ol om on oo op=
 oq or gf os ot ou gi ov ow ox gl oy oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragr=
aph=3D"">So how can we best divide the process into smaller, focused prompt=
s, each responsible for a specific part of the task? This method that I dis=
cuss in this post makes it easier to debug and fine-tune each individual co=
mponent in the flow. Additionally, no single LLM is perfect for every task.=
 It=E2=80=99s often better to divide the process into smaller tasks and ass=
ign the most suitable LLM for each, optimizing both performance and cost.</=
p><h3 id=3D"4277" class=3D"pd pe ie bc pf fz pg ga gb gc ph gd ge gf pi gg =
gh gi pj gj gk gl pk gm gn pl bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">How the La=
ngGraph Library Helps You Build Production-Ready Systems</h3><p id=3D"13c9"=
 class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok pm om on oo pn oq or gf p=
o ot ou gi pp ow ox gl pq oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">Th=
is is where the LangGraph library comes in. It offers fine-grained control =
over an agent=E2=80=99s flow and state, essential for building robust, prod=
uction-ready systems. <mark class=3D"abm abn al">LangGraph extends LangChai=
n by enabling stateful, multi-actor applications with cyclical graphs, maki=
ng it easier to build sophisticated, reliable agent runtimes.</mark></p><p =
id=3D"ea92" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok ol om on oo op=
 oq or gf os ot ou gi ov ow ox gl oy oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragr=
aph=3D"">The main key features in LangGraph are:</p><ul class=3D""><li id=
=3D"dcd6" class=3D"oh oi ie oj b ok ol om on oo op oq or gf os ot ou gi ov =
ow ox gl oy oz pa pb pr ps pt bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D""><strong cl=
ass=3D"oj if">Cycles and Branching</strong>. Implement loops and conditiona=
ls in your apps.<br>In LangGraph, each node represents an LLM agent, and th=
e edges are the communication channels between these agents. This structure=
 allows for clear and manageable workflows, where each agent performs speci=
fic tasks and passes information to other agents as needed.</li><li id=3D"9=
a7c" class=3D"oh oi ie oj b ok pu om on oo pv oq or gf pw ot ou gi px ow ox=
 gl py oz pa pb pr ps pt bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D""><strong class=
=3D"oj if">Persistent State Management</strong>. Automatically save the sta=
te after each step in the graph. Pause and resume the graph execution at an=
y point to support error recovery, human-in-the-loop workflows, time travel=
 and more.</li><li id=3D"2d69" class=3D"oh oi ie oj b ok pu om on oo pv oq =
or gf pw ot ou gi px ow ox gl py oz pa pb pr ps pt bh" data-selectable-para=
graph=3D""><strong class=3D"oj if">Human-in-the-Loop</strong>. Interrupt gr=
aph execution and give the user the option to approve or edit the following=
 action planned by the agent.</li><li id=3D"5fed" class=3D"oh oi ie oj b ok=
 pu om on oo pv oq or gf pw ot ou gi px ow ox gl py oz pa pb pr ps pt bh" d=
ata-selectable-paragraph=3D""><strong class=3D"oj if">Streaming Support</st=
rong>. Stream outputs as they are produced by each node (including token st=
reaming).</li><li id=3D"bb9f" class=3D"oh oi ie oj b ok pu om on oo pv oq o=
r gf pw ot ou gi px ow ox gl py oz pa pb pr ps pt bh" data-selectable-parag=
raph=3D""><strong class=3D"oj if">Integration with LangChain and LangSmith<=
/strong>: LangGraph integrates seamlessly with<a class=3D"ab pc" href=3D"ht=
tps://github.com/langchain-ai/langchain/" rel=3D"noopener ugc nofollow" tar=
get=3D"_blank"> LangChain</a> and<a class=3D"ab pc" href=3D"https://docs.sm=
ith.langchain.com/" rel=3D"noopener ugc nofollow" target=3D"_blank"> LangSm=
ith</a> (but does not require them).</li></ul><h3 id=3D"0c2f" class=3D"pd p=
e ie bc pf fz pg ga gb gc ph gd ge gf pi gg gh gi pj gj gk gl pk gm gn pl b=
h" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">What Did I Develop?</h3><p id=3D"674a" cl=
