j gj gk gl pk gm gn pl bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">1. Persistent Sta=
te Management</h3><pre class=3D"qa qb qc qd qe rn ro rp bm rq ay bh"><span =
id=3D"77b7" class=3D"rr pe ie ro b bd rs rt e ru rv" data-selectable-paragr=
aph=3D"">memory =3D MemorySaver()<br>self.graph =3D builder.<span class=3D"=
hljs-built_in">compile</span>(checkpointer=3Dmemory, interrupt_before=3D[<s=
pan class=3D"hljs-string">'email_sender'</span>])</span></pre><p id=3D"c014=
" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok ol om on oo op oq or gf =
os ot ou gi ov ow ox gl oy oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">A=
 crucial part of the agent=E2=80=99s design is its ability to remember its =
last state. This is managed by a MemorySaver, which ensures that if the age=
nt needs to pause and resume (e.g., while waiting for the user to decide to=
 send an email), it picks up from the correct point without starting over.<=
/p><p id=3D"cb21" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok ol om on=
 oo op oq or gf os ot ou gi ov ow ox gl oy oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-=
paragraph=3D"">There are several options for checkpointers to use in produc=
tion, such as <a class=3D"ab pc" href=3D"https://langchain-ai.github.io/lan=
ggraph/how-tos/persistence_postgres/" rel=3D"noopener ugc nofollow" target=
=3D"_blank">Postgres</a>,<a class=3D"ab pc" href=3D"https://langchain-ai.gi=
thub.io/langgraph/how-tos/persistence_mongodb/" rel=3D"noopener ugc nofollo=
w" target=3D"_blank"> MongoDB</a>, and<a class=3D"ab pc" href=3D"https://la=
ngchain-ai.github.io/langgraph/how-tos/persistence_redis/" rel=3D"noopener =
ugc nofollow" target=3D"_blank"> Redis</a>.</p><p id=3D"4bd0" class=3D"pw-p=
ost-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok ol om on oo op oq or gf os ot ou gi ov =
ow ox gl oy oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">In the app.py (w=
hich handles the UI code), a unique thread_id is generated for each session=
 to maintain the context of the user=E2=80=99s interactions. This thread_id=
 is passed along with every call to the agent, ensuring the memory state is=
 preserved across requests.</p><pre class=3D"qa qb qc qd qe rn ro rp bm rq =
ay bh"><span id=3D"6205" class=3D"rr pe ie ro b bd rs rt e ru rv" data-sele=
ctable-paragraph=3D"">            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Create a n=
ew thread ID</span><br>            thread_id =3D <span class=3D"hljs-built_=
in">str</span>(uuid.uuid4())<br>            st.session_state.thread_id =3D =
thread_id<br><br>            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Create a messag=
e from the user input</span><br>            messages =3D [HumanMessage(cont=
ent=3Duser_input)]<br>            config =3D {<span class=3D"hljs-string">'=
configurable'</span>: {<span class=3D"hljs-string">'thread_id'</span>: thre=
ad_id}}<br><br>            <span class=3D"hljs-comment"># Invoke the agent<=
/span><br>            result =3D st.session_state.agent.graph.invoke({<span=
 class=3D"hljs-string">'messages'</span>: messages}, config=3Dconfig)</span=
></pre><h3 id=3D"8662" class=3D"pd pe ie bc pf fz pg ga gb gc ph gd ge gf p=
i gg gh gi pj gj gk gl pk gm gn pl bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">2. <s=
trong class=3D"ai">Human-in-the-Loop</strong></h3><p id=3D"55ac" class=3D"p=
w-post-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok pm om on oo pn oq or gf po ot ou gi =
pp ow ox gl pq oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">The agent all=
ows human intervention at a critical decision point: Deciding whether or no=
t to send an email with the gathered travel information (flights, hotels, e=
tc). This is managed using the Human-in-the-Loop feature, which pauses the =
agent=E2=80=99s execution right before the email is sent, allowing the user=
 to review the results and provide necessary input.</p><p id=3D"1172" class=
=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok ol om on oo op oq or gf os ot o=
u gi ov ow ox gl oy oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">Implemen=
ted by passing <em class=3D"pz">interrupt_before=3D[=E2=80=98email_sender=
=E2=80=99]</em> in the graph.compile() function.</p><p id=3D"5ec4" class=3D=
"pw-post-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok ol om on oo op oq or gf os ot ou g=
i ov ow ox gl oy oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">Once the us=
er decides to send the email and submits the data, the following code runs =
in the UI to complete the process:</p><pre class=3D"qa qb qc qd qe rn ro rp=
 bm rq ay bh"><span id=3D"3be6" class=3D"rr pe ie ro b bd rs rt e ru rv" da=
ta-selectable-paragraph=3D""><span class=3D"hljs-keyword">def</span> <span =
class=3D"hljs-title.function">send_email</span>(<span class=3D"hljs-params"=
>sender_email, receiver_email, subject, thread_id</span>):<br>    <span cla=
ss=3D"hljs-keyword">try</span>:<br>        populate_envs(sender_email, rece=
iver_email, subject)<br>        config =3D {<span class=3D"hljs-string">'co=
nfigurable'</span>: {<span class=3D"hljs-string">'thread_id'</span>: thread=
_id}}<br>        st.session_state.agent.graph.invoke(<span class=3D"hljs-li=
teral">None</span>, config=3Dconfig)<br>        st.success(<span class=3D"h=
ljs-string">'Email sent successfully!'</span>)<br>        <span class=3D"hl=
js-comment"># Clear session state</span><br>        <span class=3D"hljs-key=
word">for</span> key <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">in</span> [<span class=3D=
"hljs-string">'travel_info'</span>, <span class=3D"hljs-string">'thread_id'=
</span>]:<br>            <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span> key <span c=
lass=3D"hljs-keyword">in</span> st.session_state:<br>                <span =
class=3D"hljs-keyword">del</span> st.session_state[key]</span></pre><h3 id=
=3D"fc4a" class=3D"pd pe ie bc pf fz pg ga gb gc ph gd ge gf pi gg gh gi pj=
 gj gk gl pk gm gn pl bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">3. Using Multiple =
LLMs Based on Agent State</h3><p id=3D"61ee" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragrap=
h oh oi ie oj b ok pm om on oo pn oq or gf po ot ou gi pp ow ox gl pq oz pa=
 pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">One of LangGraph=E2=80=99s key ad=
vantages is the flexibility to use multiple LLMs at different stages of the=
 workflow, rather than relying on a single LLM with one large prompt. This =
allows the agent to select the most suitable LLM based on the current task.=
 For example, you can use one LLM specialized in tool invocation and task p=
rocessing, and another that is better suited for generating and formatting =
email content in HTML.</p><h3 id=3D"3f19" class=3D"pd pe ie bc pf fz pg ga =
gb gc ph gd ge gf pi gg gh gi pj gj gk gl pk gm gn pl bh" data-selectable-p=
aragraph=3D""><strong class=3D"ai">4. </strong>Integration with LangChain a=
nd LangSmith</h3><p id=3D"6012" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph oh oi ie oj=
 b ok pm om on oo pn oq or gf po ot ou gi pp ow ox gl pq oz pa pb hf bh" da=
ta-selectable-paragraph=3D"">Integrating LangChain into your application pr=
ovides access to its comprehensive suite of tools for building complex, mod=
ular workflows with language models. By leveraging LangChain=E2=80=99s capa=
bilities, you can easily incorporate different LLMs, tools and workflows in=
to your agent=E2=80=99s functionality.</p><p id=3D"56bf" class=3D"pw-post-b=
ody-paragraph oh oi ie oj b ok ol om on oo op oq or gf os ot ou gi ov ow ox=
 gl oy oz pa pb hf bh" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">To integrate with Lan=
gSmith, simply add these environment variables to your .env file:</p><pre c=
lass=3D"qa qb qc qd qe rn ro rp bm rq ay bh"><span id=3D"8e98" class=3D"rr =
pe ie ro b bd rs rt e ru rv" data-selectable-paragraph=3D""><span class=3D"=
hljs-attr">LANGCHAIN_API_KEY</span>=3D&lt;langchain_api_key&gt;<br><span cl=
ass=3D"hljs-attr">LANGCHAIN_TRACING_V2</span>=3D<span class=3D"hljs-literal=
">true</span><br><span class=3D"hljs-attr">LANGCHAIN_PROJECT</span>=3D&lt;l=
angchain_project_name&gt;</span></pre></div></div></div><div class=3D"w cg =
